product_name: NYX Professional MakeupEpic Wear Long Lasting Liquid Eyeliner
summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsCruelty FreeGive BackLooking for a next-level liner? NYX Professional Makeup Epic Wear Liquid Liner is a waterproof, smudge-proof gel eye liner with a striking matte finish.
details: DetailsBenefitsLongwear liquid liner for face & bodyInnovative technology with silicones and polymers that bond to create a waterproof elastic film which locks in lines without smudging or smearingHigh impact colors with up to three day wearFeaturing a fine, flexible brush-tip applicator for killer precisionEasy application of countless artistic looks, from epic body paint designs to a dramatic graphic eyeliner lookThis gel liquid liner delivers semi-perm pro artistry with no crack, no bleed, no fadeCruelty freeItem 2557311How To UseApply directly to skin to draw precise lines. Let dry for a full three minutes and enjoy up to three days of wear!Pro-tips: Get creative and use your Epic Wear Liquid Liner to create waterproof body art!IngredientsIsododecane, Trimethylsiloxysilicate, Dimethicone, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Sorbitan Tristearate, Propylene Carbonate, C10-18 Triglycerides, Tin Oxide, Calcium Aluminum Borosilicate, Silica, Aluminum Hydroxide, Caprylyl Glycol, Phytosteryl Isostearate, Hexylene Glycol, Ascorbyl Palmitate, Phenoxyethanol. May Contain: CI 75470 / Carmine, CI 77007 / Ultramarines, CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499 / Iron Oxides, CI 77742 / Manganese Violet, CI 77891 / Titanium Dioxide, Mica, CI 19140 / Yellow 5 Lake, CI 42090 / Blue 1 Lake.
how_to_use: Apply directly to skin to draw precise lines. Let dry for a full three minutes and enjoy up to three days of wear!Pro-tips: Get creative and use your Epic Wear Liquid Liner to create waterproof body art!

reviews.headline: Not for me
reviews.comments: I have dry eyes and an unsteady hand.  The liquid application was hard for me to manage.

reviews.headline: This product is great
reviews.comments: This product is great for my friends who don't want eyeliner caked all over their eyelids this eyeliner was incredible and did not smudge and I wore it at an even for 12 hours. It was amazing. Wish the wand was a little better but still super good

reviews.headline: Repeat order
reviews.comments: Very good long lasting eyeliner. Does not dry out and last all day.

reviews.headline: I always get this eyeliner, does wonders
reviews.comments: I get this eyeliner every time I run out, I get 2 each time a purchase because I use a lot of eyeliner daily and it does the job. This eyeliner stays on for a long time as well, definitely worth the purchase

reviews.headline: Hard to work it
reviews.comments: I bought this not looking at it that it was waterproof. They use to sell one that wasn't which to me is the better eyeliner. If you make you make a mistake, good luck cause this does not budge. No matter what you put on it. Its good for people who don't mind it. For me I prefer the regular formula that is not waterproof.

reviews.headline: This is a pretty good eyeliner don't get me wrong!
reviews.comments: I was very excited to use this waterproof eyeliner and i swatch tested it on my hand and definitely didnt come off! I tried it on my eyes and it was MESSY. So messy ðŸ’” like i blinked and it went everywhere. When i was done i tried to take it off. It wouldnt come off and i was glad! But then it started to sting and burn and i tried to get it off frantically. It didnt come off but left me with a big stinging and burning puffy spot on my eye. It would not come off at all for many hours but it continued to burn and sting and when i blinked it would stick my eyes together. After i finally got it off both of my eyes hurt so bad ðŸ’”â€¦ now this could be user error lol. Im def not a makeup professional! I dont recommend this product for beginners. Def be careful when using it!

reviews.headline: have used it for years
reviews.comments: I wear winged eyeliner pretty much every day of the week. for years, now. the brown shade is my favorite â€” longwear, stays on no matter what, and its waterproof. the applicator isnt amazing but i use a different felt tip liner to outline my eyeliner. 10/10 i hope they never discontinue this one!

reviews.headline: Broken liner
reviews.comments: I actually have to return this because it broken. Thanks for reminding me.

reviews.headline: Best liquid eyeliner in my opinion
reviews.comments: This eyeliner is easy to apply and stays all day. This product is my favorite!

reviews.headline: Best eyeliner
reviews.comments: Omg this liquid eyeliner doesn't smear on me very pigmented i love it alot must buy

reviews.headline: Affordable an long lasting
reviews.comments: Been usung it for years and love it

reviews.headline: LIQUID EYELINER HOLY GRAIL
reviews.comments: I am an eyeliner girl (use it everyday for past 30+ years) and absolutely LOVE this eyeliner.  I discovered it last year and have bought on repeat.  if you need an eyeliner to last ALL DAY & have oily skin, this is for YOU!!!!!    I love this, PLEASE DO NOT DISCONTINUE OR CHANGE FORMULA.  it is perfect as is!!!!

reviews.headline: Dried up after a few uses
reviews.comments: I liked this product before but the last two times I have got it was a disaster. The brush and product was dried up inside on one, then the other was somewhat liquidy but dried up after 2-3 uses. Such a waste

reviews.headline: Love love love
reviews.comments: I have zero idea why the reviews are so bad this liner upholds ANYTHING I do hot Pilates and hot yoga and this even holds up in the pool. There's other water proof marked liners that suck but this is top tier I've been disappointed by every liner on the market. But the price is amazing and the quality is top tier

reviews.headline: NYX epic wear long lasting liquid eyeliner black
reviews.comments: I absolutely love the formula since its sweatproof and longlasting, the only reason I didnt give five stars is due to the thin brush applicator being flimsy, so I used an applicator from and old eyeliner. wish the brush tip applicator was sturdy and that would be perfect!!!

reviews.headline: budge proof- use clinique remover
reviews.comments: This has been my favorite eyeliner for years. It does not budge at all!!! It is hard to remove and definitely waterproof- I use clinique makeup remover and it comes right off. The applicator takes some rime to get used to but it is so worth it my makeup lasts all day. Will forever use!

reviews.headline: Best eyeliner ever created!
reviews.comments: I have been doing winged eyeliner since 2015 and by far this is the best black eyeliner I've ever used! I have hooded, teart eyes and this never smudges or transfers. At the end of the day when it's time to take it off, I just use a cleansing balm and comes of easily. By far the best eyeliner at the drugstore and beats out luxury liquids liners as well.

reviews.headline: Fantastic Eyeliner especially when starting out
reviews.comments: I started makeup not too long ago and the first eyeliners I got were not good at all. They smudged easily on my watery, hooded eyes and barely lasted the day. Not with this one. She will last you all day and even not budge when you try to take it off. When mine runs out, I will totally repurchase. Only thing is that it gets on my eyelashes when applying, but thats to expect with liquid eyeliner

reviews.headline: Best eyeliner ever!
reviews.comments: If you have oily eyelids and struggle with creasing eyeliner, this is for you! It only comes off with makeup remover or baby oil and lasts all day.

reviews.headline: Defective
reviews.comments:
Came dried out , no ink or profuct at all.
Brush was all frayed

faceoff_positive.comments: All my eyeliners have rubbed off by morning (if I didn't take them off the night before) BUT THIS IS NO NORMAL EYELINER!! I've been wearing yesterday's eyeliner all day, over 24 hour wear! (Please excuse the oily skin, I wanted to see how long the eyeliner would last so I only fixed my brows up this morning!)
faceoff_positive.headline: STAYS ON!

faceoff_negative.comments: I got this product in hopes of having a cute white liquid eyeliner, but as soon as i opened the item, the product was extremely thick and messy looking. When i tried it out, it was incredibly difficult to apply evenly and precisely. It had a very paint like consistancy and feeling. When i then tried to get it off, nothing i tried worked and it barley budged. I scrubbed my eyelids raw with soap, makeup remover, lotion, vasoline and warm water. I tried everything i could think of and it barley worked. HOURS after initially putting it on, it has rubbed off some, but none the less, is just a terribly made product. I DO NOT RECOMMEND GETTING THIS. I thought i had just got one that was in a bad batch, but after reading many other reviews of people having the same problem as myself, ive just chalked it up to the product in general.
faceoff_negative.headline: Incredibly disappointing, terribly made product.
